news.title: Country Garden liquidation hearing adjourned to January next year, court says
news.para: Ever Credit Limited, a unit of Hong Kong-listed Kingboard Holdings, filed the liquidation petition against Country Garden in February for non-payment of a $205 million loan.

news.title: Goa: SEZ land scam probe still incomplete after 10 years
news.para: In 2012, ACB registered a first information report (FIR) based on a complaint filed by Mandar Shirodkar, deputy general manager (law), Goa Industrial Development Corporation (GIDC), on “arbitrary and illegal allotment of land” to seven parties for SEZ.

news.title: Chennai development body to introduce deemed NOCs for highrise buildings
news.para: CMDA, which introduced online plan permission in May 2022, on average approves 70 plans every month and more than 70 highrise buildings every year. The numbers were 35 and 60 prior to 2022, say CMDA officials.

news.title: Shah Rukh's son buys two floors in Delhi building for Rs 37 crore
news.para: The family already owns the basement and ground floor of the building, where Khan and his wife Gauri used to live in the early days.

news.title: EQT emerges as top contender to acquire Aavas Financiers
news.para: EQT is competing with two other private equity peers, CVC Capital Partners and Bain Capital, ahead of binding offers that are expected early August as PE firms look to consolidate their position in the fast-growing sector.

news.title: Billionaire battle heats up as Adani challenges Birla in cement
news.para: India's cement industry is witnessing an intense battle as Gautam Adani's expansion efforts trigger a race with Kumar Mangalam Birla's UltraTech Cement Ltd. Both billionaires are striving to dominate the supply of cement, crucial for India's infrastructure boom. In less than two years, Adani and UltraTech have completed six deals, with UltraTech announcing a seventh acquisition of a key regional player.

news.title: Noida authority plans to allot 5.5 lakh sq meter land in FY25, raise Rs 3,800 crore revenue
news.para: The land allocation is projected to generate a revenue of Rs 3,795 crore. The Authority has decided on this ambitious target despite managing to allot only 23% of its land target last year.

news.title: SC seeks information on affordable home projects allowed in Haryana in 10 years
news.para: The court was hearing petitions filed by buyers who have invested around Rs 160 crore in Mahira Homes in Sector 103 - a project that has been stalled for almost two years and a half.

news.title: L&T Realty, Valor Estate to jointly develop Rs 20,000 crore project in Mumbai
news.para: Both companies are planning to build a mixed-use project with premium housing, commercial spaces, and a 1,000-key five-star luxury hotel, on a combination of revenue and area-share basis.

news.title: UltraTech to acquire India Cement; buy 32.72% promoters' stake for Rs 3,954 crore
news.para: With an installed capacity of 154.86 million tonnes per annum (MTPA) of grey cement, UltraTech Cement leads the Indian cement industry. It has an ambition to become one of the largest cement companies in the world and and has set a target for 200 MTPA.

news.title: Gwalior: Residents of Golden Tower left homeless and furious
news.para: While people associated with the builder claim that one of the residents used a drill machine near the main pillar to clear waterlogging causing it to tilt, residents are looking forward to a serious action against the builder identified as Mohan Bandil accusing him for poor construction work of the building .

news.title: DLF Cyber City Developers' office rental income rises 11% to Rs 942 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: According to the latest investor presentation, DLF Cyber City Developers' rental income from office buildings rose to Rs 942 crore during the April-June period of the current fiscal from Rs 851 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Delhi HC orders CBI probe into repeated PILs on unauthorised constructions
news.para: A bench of Acting Chief Justice Manmohan and Justice Tushar Rao Gedela decided to rope in CBI after it came across a law student who filed 42 petitions against illegal construction, but less than half were eventually listed before the court for hearing.

news.title: GIS mapping completed in four municipal areas: Goa urban development minister
news.para: Rane said that Kolbro Group pvt ltd, the agency appointed by govt, is currently conducting GIS-based mapping for the Corporation of the City of Panaji (CCP) and Sankhali municipal council.

news.title: Kerala announces major modifications to land disposal regulations for industrial allocation
news.para: The amendments in the regulations governing the industrial land allocation by the Kerala Industrial Infrastructure Development Corporation (KINFRA) and the Kerala State Industrial Development Corporation (KSIDC) aim to create a more industry-friendly environment.

news.title: Gurugram: Raze & rebuild cycle of farmhouses ensures Raisina never heals
news.para: It's not just razed buildings that are being rebuilt. More protected land has been cleared, new roads have come up, and electricity poles are being erected.

news.title: Maharashtra: Housing societies on leasehold plots can shift to freehold at 5-10% of RR rate
news.para: In March, the govt had granted the same concession to housing societies on both types of land. But two days later, on March 18, through a gazette notification, the concession for leasehold plots was withdrawn.

news.title: Anant Raj's net profit rise 63.5% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Anant Raj Limited announced a 63.5% rise in profit after tax for Q1 FY2025, totaling ₹42.28 crores. Total income improved by 50.9% to ₹284.29 crores, despite an increase in total expenses to ₹227.43 crores. Profit before tax saw a 62.8% boost to ₹56.86 crores compared to the previous year. These results showcase substantial growth.

news.title: Bombay HC directs KDMC chief & Thane police commissioner to demolish unauthorised building
news.para: “...together, the two commissioners must ensure that rule of law prevails and lawful orders of the corporation and this court are not frustrated by rule of the mob,” said a bench of Justices Mahesh Sonak and Kamal Khata.

news.title: Star Housing Finance reports 94% rise in profit in Q1 FY25
news.para: Assets under management soared by 73.55 per cent to Rs 471.41 crore in the June quarter over the year-ago period. Disbursements were at Rs 61.23 crore in the quarter under review.
